This paper deals with energy-efficient beamforming in multi-cell multi-user MIMO systems, which involves the use of information theory, networking, and optimization techniques. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are likely sub-categories. The paper also focuses on the use of multiple antennas at user terminals, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves optimizing the use of transmission resources, which is related to game theory and falls under the sub-category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
